---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="USCitizenship2032 - A Better Path Forward">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-dark py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <p class="text-gold-500 font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-6">A Proposed 28th Amendment</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-warm-white max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-tight mb-6">
        It's Time to <span class="gold-accent">Modernize</span> Birthright Citizenship
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-warm-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        We looked at 30 countries. Only 3 give automatic citizenship just for being born there.
        The U.S. is one of them. There's a better way.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/amendment" class="btn-primary">Read the Proposal</a>
        <a href="/comparison" class="btn-secondary">See How the World Does It</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Core Idea -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Not Left. Not Right. <span class="text-teal-600">Forward.</span></h2>
        <p class="text-warm-gray text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Right now, the debate is stuck. One side says "change nothing." The other side tries executive orders that get blocked in court. This is a third option, based on how most of the world already works.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-teal-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Qualified at Birth</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            If you're born in the U.S. and at least one parent is a citizen or green card holder, you're a citizen at birth. This is how it works in the UK, Australia, and New Zealand.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gold-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-gold-600 text-xl font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">10-Year Path to Citizenship</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            If neither parent qualifies, the child gets protected status. After living in the U.S. for 10 years, they become a full citizen automatically. No child who grows up here gets left behind.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-teal-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">No Child Left Stateless</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            If a child is born on U.S. soil and would have no citizenship anywhere in the world, the U.S. steps in. No child born here will ever be a person without a country.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Stats -->
  <section class="bg-charcoal py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gold-500 mb-2">3 of 30</p>
          <p class="text-warm-white/60">Countries give automatic birthright citizenship</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gold-500 mb-2">16 of 30</p>
          <p class="text-warm-white/60">Countries only give citizenship through parents, including every Nordic country</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gold-500 mb-2">Jan 1, 2032</p>
          <p class="text-warm-white/60">Start date. No one born before this is affected.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Partisan Bridge -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Built for Both Sides</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-gray text-lg text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        This is not a compromise where everyone loses. Each side gets something they have never been able to get before.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-block w-8 h-1 bg-teal-600 rounded"></span>
            If You Lean Right
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-5 text-warm-gray">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-teal-600 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">Sovereignty.</strong> America decides who is American, not a lucky plane ticket. This matches Japan, Switzerland, and the UK.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-teal-600 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">Ends birth tourism.</strong> Closes the loophole where a short visit can lead to a lifetime of benefits.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-teal-600 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">Based on commitment.</strong> Children are born into families who are already part of the American system.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-block w-8 h-1 bg-gold-500 rounded"></span>
            If You Lean Left
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-5 text-warm-gray">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gold-500 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">Puts the Dream Act in the Constitution.</strong> The 10-year path means no child raised in American schools is ever deported. Ever.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gold-500 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">No more executive order chaos.</strong> A constitutional amendment cannot be undone by the next president.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gold-500 font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <span><strong class="text-near-black">No child left without a country.</strong> The U.S. guarantees in writing that no child born here will be stateless.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What This Does NOT Do -->
  <section class="bg-teal-50 py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10">What This Does <span class="text-teal-600">NOT</span> Do</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5 text-left">
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-5">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-lg font-bold shrink-0">&times;</span>
          <span>Does <strong>not</strong> deport anyone. Ever.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-5">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-lg font-bold shrink-0">&times;</span>
          <span>Does <strong>not</strong> affect anyone born before Jan 1, 2032</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-5">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-lg font-bold shrink-0">&times;</span>
          <span>Does <strong>not</strong> create a tracking system or registry</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-5">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-lg font-bold shrink-0">&times;</span>
          <span>Does <strong>not</strong> remove any existing path to citizenship</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start bg-white rounded-lg border border-light-gray p-5 sm:col-span-2 sm:max-w-md sm:mx-auto">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-lg font-bold shrink-0">&times;</span>
          <span>Does <strong>not</strong> change how legal immigration works</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container text-center max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Join the Conversation</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-white/70 text-lg mb-8">
        This proposal is open source. Read it, challenge it, make it better.
        The best ideas win, not the loudest voices.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/amendment" class="btn-primary">Read the Full Amendment</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032/issues/new/choose" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-secondary">Give Feedback on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
